                "message": "Try to fix GraalPy CI memory usage\n\nWe're seeing periodic test failures of the GraalPy run with\n\n> The hosted runner lost communication with the server. Anything in your workflow that terminates the runner process, starves it for CPU/Memory, or blocks its network access can cause this error.\n\nI don't really know what's causing it, but my initial assumption\nis memory.\n\nThe is an uninformed attempt to fix that. To do so I've:\n* force the GC to run before each compilation. (We already force\n  it after each \"run\" test, but let's assume that cleaning up\n  after the Cython compilation might be the problem here).\n* Make the `ProcessPoolExecutor` periodically restart the\n  processes (on the assumption that we're gradually accumulating\n  memory leaks somewhere).\n\nI've got no idea if this will work but it at least seems worth\na try.",
